  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ Gas 6</p><p>Peel and halve the <strong>red onions</strong>, then slice <strong>1</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2]</span><strong> onion half<span class=\"text-danger\">[ves]</span></strong> and finely chop the <strong>remaining onion</strong></p><p>Heat a pot over a low heat with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>finely</strong> <strong>chopped onion</strong> (save the sliced onion for later!) with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>ground</strong> <strong>sumac </strong>and cook for 20-25 min, stirring frequently, or until soft and caramelised – these are your <strong>caramelised onions</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
